workflow.name: Automate Google Meet notes with GPT-4.1-mini, Notion, Slack & Gmail distribution
workflow.description:
üßæ An intelligent automation system that turns **Google Meet** recordings into structured meeting notes ‚Äî integrating **Fireflies.ai**, **OpenAI GPT-4.1-mini**, **Notion**, **Slack**, **Google Drive**, and **Gmail** via **n8n**.

üé• **Demo:** [Watch the Loom walkthrough](https://www.loom.com/share/f1277351e6de412caf32e12f15a2cacd?sid=a8f7e583-d5a8-496b-9299-08f66a51334f)

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è What It Does

The **Google Meet Notes Generator & Distributor** automates the entire post-meeting workflow.

**Workflow Summary:**

1. Fetches **Google Meet transcript** via Fireflies.ai webhook.
2. Aggregates and summarizes transcript using **OpenAI GPT-4.1-mini** into:

   * Title
   * Summary
   * Decisions
   * Action Items
   * Risks
   * Questions
3. Stores the **transcript as a text file** on Google Drive and generates a shareable link.
4. Creates a **Notion page** with all the meeting details.
5. Posts the summary in `#meeting` Slack channel.
6. DMs each attendee on Slack with personalized meeting notes.
7. Sends **email recap** to all attendees via Gmail.

**Result:** No more manual note-taking or scattered updates ‚Äî everything centralized, formatted, and instantly shareable.

---

## üí° Use Cases

| Scenario                    | Description                                                                             |
| --------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Team Meeting Summaries**  | Automatically summarize and distribute meeting notes for internal teams.                |
| **Project Management**      | Keep structured decisions, action items, and risks documented for each project meeting. |
| **Remote Teams**            | Notify distributed teams in Slack and via email without extra effort.                   |
| **Client Updates**          | Share polished meeting summaries with clients instantly.                                |
| **Knowledge Base / Notion** | Archive structured notes in Notion for reference and compliance.                        |

---

## üîß Setup

### 1. **Accounts and Tools Needed**

| Tool                       | Purpose                                        |
| -------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| **ü§ñ Fireflies.ai API**    | Fetch Google Meet transcripts via webhook      |
| **üß† OpenAI API**          | Summarize and structure transcript into notes  |
| **üìì Notion API**          | Create structured meeting pages                |
| **üí¨ Slack OAuth/Bot**     | Post summaries in channel and DM attendees     |
| **üóÇ Google Drive OAuth2** | Store transcripts and generate shareable links |
| **‚úâÔ∏è Gmail OAuth2**        | Email meeting recaps to attendees              |

---

### 2. **Fireflies.ai Setup**

1. Get API key from Fireflies.ai.
2. Configure **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí Fireflies API**.
3. Ensure webhook triggers are set to send `meetingId` to n8n.

---

### 3. **OpenAI Setup**

1. Generate API key at [OpenAI](https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys).
2. Add to **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí OpenAI API**.
3. Use model **GPT-4.1-mini** in `Agent` and `Generate Slack Message` nodes.

---

### 4. **Notion Setup**

1. Create a Notion integration and share your workspace.
2. Add API token in **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí Notion API**.
3. Map workspace/page IDs to `Notion Page` node.

---

### 5. **Slack Setup**

1. Create Slack Bot in workspace with **chat:write** and **users:read** permissions.
2. Add OAuth token in **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí Slack API**.
3. Connect to `Send a message #meeting` and `DMs to Attendees` nodes.

---

### 6. **Google Drive Setup**

1. Create a folder for transcripts.
2. Enable Google Drive API in **Google Cloud Console**.
3. Add OAuth2 credentials to **n8n ‚Üí Google Drive**.

---

### 7. **Gmail Setup**

1. Enable Gmail API in Google Cloud.
2. Add OAuth2 credentials in **n8n ‚Üí Gmail**.
3. Connect to `Email to Attendees` node.

---

### 8. **n8n Workflow Setup**

1. Import provided n8n workflow JSON.
2. Configure all credentials: Fireflies, OpenAI, Notion, Slack, Google Drive, Gmail.
3. Activate workflow.
4. Test by sending a meeting ID via webhook.

**Workflow automatically:**
**Fetch ‚Üí Summarize ‚Üí Store ‚Üí Notion ‚Üí Slack ‚Üí DM ‚Üí Email**

---

## üß† Result

A fully automated AI pipeline that transforms Google Meet recordings into polished, shareable meeting notes ‚Äî eliminating manual note-taking and keeping your team informed in real time.

---

## üìû Support & Contact

If you face any issues during setup or execution, contact:

üîó **LinkedIn:** [Atharva Jaiswal](https://www.linkedin.com/in/atharva-jaiswal/)

parameters.text:
=You are given a transcript of a meeting. Extract and structure the output into a single JSON object.  

Rules:  
- Output only one JSON object.  
- Do not use arrays.  
- For multiple items (decisions, action_items, risks, questions), join them into a single string separated by line breaks ("\n").  
- Each item must start with a dash and a space ("- ") to make it a bullet list.  
- Required fields: title, summary, decisions, action_items, risks, questions.  
- title and summary = plain strings.  
- decisions, action_items, risks, questions = single strings with line breaks between items, each prefixed by "- ".  
- Do not include any explanatory text outside of the JSON.  

Format:
{
"title": "...",
"summary": "...",
"decisions": "- Decision 1\n- Decision 2",
"action_items": "- Action 1\n- Action 2\n- Action 3",
"risks": "- Risk 1\n- Risk 2",
"questions": "- Question 1\n- Question 2"
}

Input: {{ $('Aggregate').item.json.raw_text }}

values.content:
=You are given a structured meeting JSON (title, summary, decisions, action_items, risks, questions).

Task:  
Write a short, well-formatted Slack message for the #meeting-notes channel.

Rules: 
-Follow the format correctly
-Use relvent emojis for Key Decisions points 
-do not add anything in notion and drive link it should be consistent no extra brackets 
Example 1:
üìù Sprint Review and Release Planning Meeting
The team reviewed last sprint's achievements including the client dashboard integration and QA completion on staging.

‚ú® Key Decisions:
‚Ä¢ üöÄ Release dashboard tomorrow at 2:00pm
‚Ä¢ üìä Analytics module release to follow in next sprint

üîó Notion: https://www.notion.so/Sprint-Review-and-Release-Planning-Meeting-25d0bc030f368127bfd2fa0bc5fa29a6

üìÇ Drive: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ypTXN47oqRFHKXK4G6lTjpRfFIQp3o3f/view

Actual Input
Title:{{ $('Agent').item.json.output.title }}
Summary: {{ $('Agent').item.json.output.summary }}
Notion Link:{{ $json.url }}
Drive Link:{{ $('Drive Link').item.json.drive_link }}
